    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe [LSP RPC request parser](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/rpc.lua#L66) fails to parse headers where more than one field exists even though `parse_headers` supports multiple fields. The [protocol](https://microsoft.github.io/language-server-protocol/specifications/lsp/3.17/specification/#headerPart) requires the header to be terminated with `\\r\\n` and for at least one header field to be included. The implementation of this parser assumes that the header is complete when there exists `\\r\\n\\r\\n` which happens to be true for popular language servers.\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\n1. Apply the [patch](https://gist.github.com/dssecret/c052154ca61fca5298b4a5a733bb80e2)\r\n2. Execute respective test with `TEST_FILE=test/functional/plugin/lsp_spec.lau TEST_FILTER='handler can return false as response' make functionaltest`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n_No response_\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-438+g1f2f460b4-dirty\n\n### Language server name/version\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nManjaro 24.0.4\n\n### Log file\n\n_No response_",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I don't really see anything wrong in the code. Headers can be split by `\\r\\n` and after the last header there must be an extra `\\r\\n` to separate headers from body. This is in line with the specification as far as I can tell:\r\n\r\n> Considering the last header field and the overall header itself are each terminated with ‘\\r\\n’, and that at least one header is mandatory, **this means that two ‘\\r\\n’ sequences always immediately precede the content part of a message**.`\r\n\r\nYour patched test case looks wrong. It would need to include the additional `\\r\\n`. E.g.:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nsocket:write(table.concat({ 'Content-Length: ', tostring(#msg), '\\r\\nContent-Type: application/vscode-jsonrpc; charset=utf-8\\r\\n\\r\\n', msg }))\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n",
